column5: Had a great day out on the lake.  I was fishing solo and my camera died so I had to take pics with my phone.  Nice fish and none of them had clipped fins. The biggest fish was big and almost took 10 mins to get in.  Very strong and very fat.  It was a new PB lake trout for me. My fishing rod is 28" long Here they are from smallest to largest.  Caught all fish fro 10:30 am to 1 pm.  All fish were released.  fish 2  fish 3  Biggest fish   sometimes Simcoe can be very rewarding but other days so frustrating
That's a great day. Nice going.
Very nice Chris... a day well played!
Very nice, hopefully we fair as well today
Awesome.... that last one looks like a tuna  Burt
very nice , some solid lakers there for sure
